{{zh-forms|alt=圅,凾}}

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally {{zh-l|*圅}}, a {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} – an upside-down arrow stored inside a box with one or two handles.

===Etymology===
According to {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, derived from {{och-l|含|to have in the mouth, hold inside}}. Note also potential similarities to {{ncog|my|ခွံ|t=shell}} ({{zh-ref|Luce, 1981}}).

